    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nahua tlahuiztli (insignia) in the form of large umbrella-shaped feathered structures worn on a back-frame. These were prestigious gifts presented to nobles made in a variety of colors, and was frequently topped with an effigy head of the deity Xolotl; hence its name, "Xolotl-head." This insignia also represents the altepetl of Tepeticpac, Tlaxcala.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
